PageTitle: undo snmp-agent trap enable feature-name trap-name
FuncDef:
The undo snmp-agent trap enable feature-name trap-name command disables the trap function for the OSPFv3 module.
By default, the trap function for the OSPFv3 module is disabled.
CLIs: undo snmp-agent trap enable feature-name <feature-name-val> trap-name { ospfv3ifconfigerror | ospfv3ifrxbadpacket | ospfv3ifstatechange | ospfv3nbrrestarthelperstatuschange | ospfv3nbrstatechange }

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies a feature name.
The value is a string of 1 to 7 case-insensitive characters, spaces not supported.

Indicates that OSPFv3 interface configurations are inconsistent.
-

Indicates that an OSPFv3 interface received an error packet.
-

Indicates that the OSPFv3 interface status changed.
-

Indicates that a neighbor's restart status changed during GR.
-

Indicates that the OSPFv3 neighbor status changed.
-

Examples: [~HUAWEI] undo snmp-agent trap enable feature-name ospfv3 trap-name ospfv3nbrstatechange
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To disable the traps of one or more events, you can specify trap-name.
